This paper proposes a universal part-of-speech tagset and a mapping from 25 different treebank tagsets to this universal set, which is relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses experiments on unsupervised grammar induction, which involves machine learning and could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves data processing and standardization, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
